+    /// timeSeriesIncreaseToGrid reuses the ExtrapolatedValue kernel with the
+    /// rate counter-correction (is_rate=true) but WITHOUT the divide-by-window
+    /// (is_increase=true). The alias pins is_increase so the generic factory
+    /// (which only threads is_rate) still produces a five-arg template-template.
+    FunctionDocumentation::Description description_timeSeriesIncreaseToGrid = R"(
+Aggregate function that takes time series data as pairs of timestamps and values and calculates [PromQL-like increase](https://prometheus.io/docs/prometheus/latest/querying/functions/#increase) from this data on a regular time grid described by start timestamp, end timestamp and step.
+For each point on the grid the samples for calculating `increase` are considered within the specified time window. `increase` is `rate` multiplied by the window length: it is the counter-reset-corrected, boundary-extrapolated total increase over the window, not divided by the window seconds.
+
+:::warning
+This function is experimental, enable it by setting `allow_experimental_ts_to_grid_aggregate_function=true`.
+:::
+    )";
